  "title": "Newtons third law - elephant pushing boxes",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two blocks, A and B, on a horizontal surface. Block A is to the left of Block B and is smaller than it, and the two blocks are in contact with one another. An elephant pushes to the right into the left side of Block A.\" src=\"/images/cacc089f888cc2fa0d772804f82bf343.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">An elephant pushes two heavy boxes across a rough surface. The force that Box <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> exerts on Box <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub A B\"><math alttext=\"F sub A B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>AB</mtext></msub></math></span></span> and the force that Box <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> exerts on Box <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub B A\"><math alttext=\"F sub B A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>BA</mtext></msub></math></span></span>. Which of the following statements indicates the correct reasoning to support the claim that <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the absolute value of F sub A B, equals the absolute value of F sub B A\"><math alttext=\"the absolute value of F sub A B, equals the absolute value of F sub B A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>AB</mtext></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo><mo>=</mo><mpadded><mo>|</mo><mpadded><msub><mi>F</mi><mtext>BA</mtext></msub></mpadded><mo>|</mo></mpadded></mpadded></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">This claim is true only if the boxes are moving with a constant velocity.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">This claim is true only if the masses are equal.</p>",
